<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">25</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2005</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">997</span> - <span property="pageEnd">1015</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16009820/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16009820</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2005.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2005</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.254045035">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=PDH+%3D+paraduodenal+hernia&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">PDH = paraduodenal hernia</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=SBO+%3D+small+bowel+obstruction&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">SBO = small bowel obstruction</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Knowledge of the anatomy of the peritoneal cavity and the characteristic anatomic location and CT findings of each type of internal hernia may assist in identification of internal hernias in most cases of small bowel obstruction.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Nobuyuki</span> <span property="familyName">Takeyama</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (N.T., T.G., Y.O., T.H., H.M.) and General and Gastrointestinal Surgery (M.K.), Showa University School of Medicine, 1-5-8 Hatanodai, Shinagawa-ku, Tokyo 142-8666, Japan; the Departments of Radiology (S.S.) and Surgery (K.H.), Yokohama Asahi Chuo General Hospital, Yokohama, Japan; the Department of Surgery, Kikuna Memorial Hospital, Yokohama, Japan (H.K.); and the Department of Surgery, Totsuka Kyouritsu Hospital, Yokohama, Japan (M.N.). Recipient of a Certificate of Merit award for an education exhibit at the 2003 RSNA Annual Meeting. Received March 12, 2004; revision requested April 8; final revision received September 30; accepted October 5. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Takeyama/Nobuyuki" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Takehiko</span> <span property="familyName">Gokan</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (N.T., T.G., Y.O., T.H., H.M.) and General and Gastrointestinal Surgery (M.K.), Showa University School of Medicine, 1-5-8 Hatanodai, Shinagawa-ku, Tokyo 142-8666, Japan; the Departments of Radiology (S.S.) and Surg